source: On va se faire cuire un œuf !
references: ["Let's go make some omelets!"]
hypothesis: We're going to cook an egg!

source: J'ai eu la banane !
references: ['I got the banana.']
hypothesis: I had the banana!

source: La creme a la banane est la première a partir.
references: ["Banana cream's the first to go."]
hypothesis: The banana cream is the first to go.

source: - Papa, puis-je avoir les patates ?
references: ['- Dad, may I please have the potatoes?']
hypothesis: - Dad, can I have the potatoes?

source: Il y a les patates des Guignard et il y a les miennes.
references: ['My potatoes are different.']
hypothesis: There are the Guignard potatoes and there are mine.

source: Je suis certain que c'est la meilleure de leurs 57 enseignes "qui ont la patate" ! *
references: ['Yes, I\'m sure this is the best of their 57 "spudtacular" east coast locations.']
hypothesis: I'm sure it's the best of their 57 "who have the potato" signs! *

source: J'ai gardé le reçu pour prouver que j'ai les patates Laratte.
references: ['I brought the receipt to prove I got Laratte potatoes.']
hypothesis: I kept the receipt to prove that I have the Laratte potatoes.

source: Je peux avoir les patates ?
references: ['May I have the potatoes, please?']
hypothesis: Can I have the potatoes?

source: Si je suis là, tu auras le coup de foudre
references: ["If I'm there, you'll feel the thunder"]
hypothesis: If I'm here you'll fall in love

source: Comment a-t-il été frappé par la foudre... lors d'une tempête sans coups de foudre repertoriés ?
references: ['How did he get struck by lightning... during a storm with no recorded lightning strikes?']
hypothesis: How was it struck by lightning... in a storm with no listed lightning strikes?

source: Tu me parlais du coup de foudre...
references: ['Remember how you told me about lightning striking?']
hypothesis: You were telling me about love at first sight...

source: Ce dernier coup de foudre a grillé mon générateur.
references: ['That last lightning strike fried my generator.']
hypothesis: That last bolt of lightning fried my generator.

source: Ce n'était pas un coup de foudre, ça semblait... évident.
references: ["It wasn't like a bolt of lightening it just seemed... obvious."]
hypothesis: It wasn't love at first sight, it seemed...obvious.

source: Moi, j'ai bien une idée... Vous donnez votre langue au chat ? Couper le courant.
references: ['Okay, okay, so, then, let me throw this out there and see if the cat licks it up: we cut the power.']
hypothesis: Me, I have an idea... You give your tongue to the cat? Cut power.

source: On pourrait refaire le pont du Queen Elizabeth 2 avec tout ce bois.
references: ['You could deck the QE 2 with the wood they gave me.']
hypothesis: We could redo the deck of the Queen Elizabeth 2 with all that wood.

source: Mais j'essaie de faire le pont.
references: ["But I've been trying to do a backbend."]
hypothesis: But I try to make the bridge.

source: Tu veux faire le pont ?
references: ['You want to do it backwards?']
hypothesis: Want to bridge?

source: Je suis pour faire le pont réparé.
references: ["I'm to get the bridge repaired."]
hypothesis: I'm for getting the bridge repaired.

source: Faisons le pont !
references: ['Set up the bridge!']
hypothesis: Let's make the bridge!

source: Il n'y a pas de chats.
references: ['There are no cats.']
hypothesis: There are no cats.

source: Il n'y a pas un chat dans les rues, encore moins de palanquins.
references: ["There's not a cat in the streets, much less a palanquin."]
hypothesis: There is not a spade in the streets, let alone palanquins.

source: Il n'y a pas un chaton quelque part qui a besoin d'une manucure ?
references: ["Isn't there a kitten somewhere that needs a manicure?"]
hypothesis: Is there a kitten out there that needs a manicure?

source: Mais il n'y a pas de chat.
references: ['Only there is no cat.']
hypothesis: But there is no cat.

source: - Il n'y a pas de chaton.
references: ['- There is no kitten.']
hypothesis: - There is no kitten.

source: - Jette l'éponge !
references: ['Throw the towel! Throw the towel!']
hypothesis: - Throws in the towel !

source: - Les carottes sont cuites ?
references: ['The carrots are cooked?']
hypothesis: - The carrots are cooked ?

source: Oui. "Les carottes sont cuites."
references: ['Yes. "The carrots are cooked."']
hypothesis: Yes. "The carrots are cooked."

source: Les carottes sont cuites!
references: ["That soup's gonna boil!"]
hypothesis: The carrots are cooked!

source: Cette fois, les carottes sont cuites.
references: ['This time, the carrots are cooked.']
hypothesis: This time the carrots are cooked.

source: Les carottes sont cuites !
references: ['The carrots are cooked!']
hypothesis: The carrots are cooked !

source: J'écris pas "Bises, Stephanie" à quelqu'un qui a le doigt dans le nez tout le temps.
references: ['I can\'t sign, "Love, Stephanie" to someone who has his finger in his nose all day.']
hypothesis: I don't write "Bises, Stephanie" to someone who has the finger in the nose all the time.

source: Pourquoi tu te mets autant les doigts dans le nez ?
references: ['Why do you have to pick your nose so much?']
hypothesis: Why are you putting your fingers in your nose so much?

source: Je rêve parfois que je t'agraffe les doigts dans le nez.
references: ['I have dreams where I staple your fingers to your face.']
hypothesis: I sometimes dream that I'm stapling your fingers in your nose.

source: - Et me mettre les doigts dans le nez?
references: ['Can I pick my nose?']
hypothesis: - And stick my fingers in my nose?

source: T'as encore le doigt dans le nez!
references: ['You still have the finger in the nose!']
hypothesis: You still have your finger in the nose!

source: Je n'y vois que du feu Cliquetis
references: ['# All I see are stars #']
hypothesis: All I see is fire

source: - Je n'y vois que du feu
references: ['# All I see are stars #']
hypothesis: - I see nothing but fire

source: L pensent que ce n'est pas votre tasse de thé.
references: ['I think this is not your cup of tea.']
hypothesis: l think this is not your cup of tea.

source: - Ce n'est pas votre tasse de thé?
references: ['Not your cup of tea?']
hypothesis: - Not your cup of tea?

source: On dirait du pipi de chat.
references: ['It tastes like cat pee.']
hypothesis: Looks like cat pee.

source: Vous sentez le pipi de chat.
references: ['You smell like cat piss.']
hypothesis: You smell cat pee.

source: Je me plains pas, mais t'es plus celle qui a parfumé mes habits au pipi de chat.
references: ["- I'm not complaining. I think it's wonderful, I really do... but you are not the same girl who made all my clothes smell like cat pee."]
hypothesis: I'm not complaining, but you're not the one who perfumed my clothes with cat pee anymore.

source: Vos têtes sont remplies pipi de chat.
references: ['Your heads are filled with cat urine.']
hypothesis: Your heads are filled with cat pee.

source: Elle a 5 chats, sa maison doit sentir le pipi de chat au lieu de la bière et de la fumée.
references: ['She has five cats, so her place probably smells like cat pee instead of beer and smoke.']
hypothesis: She has 5 cats, her house must smell of cat pee instead of beer and smoke.

source: Mais qui prendra la tête des forces de Rome ?
references: ['Yet who shall lead the forces of Rome?']
hypothesis: But who will lead the forces of Rome?

source: Alors comment vous prévoyiez de prendre la tête ?
references: ['So how do you plan to take the lead?']
hypothesis: So how did you plan to take the lead?

source: Il prendra la tête, mais je ne crois pas qu'il tiendra la distance.
references: ["He's gonna be out on the lead, but I don't think he'll handle the distance."]
hypothesis: He will take the lead, but I don't think he will go the distance.

source: Prenez la tête!
references: ['Lean forward!']
hypothesis: Take the lead!

source: Prenez la tête.
references: ['Go ahead.']
hypothesis: Take the lead.

source: C'est la fin des haricots!
references: ['This is the end of the beans!']
hypothesis: It is the end of beans!

source: Nous avons perdu beaucoup de temps à essayer de comprendre l'âme, ...alors que la partie matérielle de notre être, reste une terre inconnue.
references: ['We wasted so much time trying to study the soul meanwhile the material element of our beings is still an unknown universe.']
hypothesis: We have wasted a lot of time trying to understand the soul, while the material part of our being remains uncharted territory.

source: Mon boulot, c'est de prendre les âmes
references: ['I take souls for a living.']
hypothesis: My job is to take souls

source: Ca fait quoi de prendre l'âme de quelqu'un ?
references: ["What is it like to take someone's soul?"]
hypothesis: How does it feel to take someone's soul?

source: On peut prendre l'âme des arbres ?
references: ['Can you take tree souls?']
hypothesis: Can we take the souls of trees?

source: JE prends les âmes des gens avant qu'ils meurent.
references: ["I take people's souls before they die."]
hypothesis: I take people's souls before they die.

source: Je suis sûr qu'ils ont construit cet endroit pour qu'ils s'envoient en l'air.
references: ['Sure hope they built this place to code.']
hypothesis: I'm sure they built this place to get laid.

source: On s'envoie en l'air.
references: ['Here we are, up in the air.']
hypothesis: We take off.

source: Ce n'est pas encore le moment de fêter ni de s'envoyer en l'air.
references: ["Well, let's don't start jumping up and down, throwing babies in the air yet, Captain."]
hypothesis: It's not the time to celebrate or get laid yet.

source: C'est vrai qu'un mouton peut se noyer dans un verre d'eau ?
references: ['You once told me a cup of fresh water was enough to drown a sheep, right?']
hypothesis: Is it true that a sheep can drown in a glass of water?

source: Il se noie dans un verre d'eau.
references: ['This man would drown in a glass of water.']
hypothesis: He drowns in a glass of water.

source: Tu sens le sapin.
references: ['You smell like a pine cone.']
hypothesis: You smell the tree.

source: Ça sentait le sapin.
references: ['I smelled that pine box.']
hypothesis: It smelled of fir.

source: - Si on tournait la page ?
references: ["- Let's turn the page."]
hypothesis: - How about we turn the page?

source: Bon OK, continuer de tourner les pages.
references: ['All right, keep flipping pages.']
hypothesis: Okay, keep turning the pages.

source: - Il tourne les pages à l'envers.
references: ['It keeps turning the pages back.']
hypothesis: - He turns the pages upside down.

source: Retourne la page.
references: ['Oy. Turn it over.']
hypothesis: Returns the page.

source: Écoute, chéri. Si la musique te plaît, viens me tourner les pages.
references: ['Darling, if you like the music, sit beside me and turn the pages.']
hypothesis: Listen, honey. If you like the music, come and turn the pages.

source: Et que ça tourne au vinaigre ?
references: ['And watch it turn to vinegar?']
hypothesis: And it turns sour?

source: L'eau devient amère avec le poison, le vin tourne au vinaigre.
references: ['Water grows bitter with poison, Wine turns into vinegar.']
hypothesis: Water becomes bitter with poison, wine turns to vinegar.

source: tous crachent sur toi, mais tu n'es pas prête.
references: ["Everyone's spitting at you, but you're not ready."]
hypothesis: everyone spits on you, but you're not ready.

source: Il refusait même de prendre une bouchée de pain.
references: ['Refused to take even a mouthful of bread.']
hypothesis: He refused even to take a bite of bread.

source: Tout ça pour une bouchée de pain ?
references: ["What's a loaf of bread anyway?"]
hypothesis: All that for a pittance?

source: Nous étions 14 enfants... et nous devions nous battre à table pour avoir une bouchée de pain.
references: ['There were 14 children. And we had to fight for our bread at the table:']
hypothesis: We were 14 children... and we had to fight at the table to have a bite to eat.

source: Ca sent comme si quelqu'un était crevé ici...
references: ['It smells like something died down here.']
hypothesis: It smells like someone's knackered here...

source: Il y a ce moment excellent où son œil est crevé...
references: ["There's this brilliant bit where his eye gets gouged out..."]
hypothesis: There is this excellent moment when his eye is gouged out...

source: Il y en a qui sont crevés !
references: ['What the hell? Half of them are dead.']
hypothesis: There are some who are exhausted!

source: Mais vous êtes crevés.
references: ["Wish you could try it, but you're all dead."]
hypothesis: But you are exhausted.

source: T'es dans la lune ?
references: ['Are you on the moon?']
hypothesis: Are you on the moon?

source: Enfin, Arthur, tu es dans la lune depuis deux mois.
references: ["God! Arthur, you've been gazing at the moon for the past two months."]
hypothesis: Finally, Arthur, you've been in the moon for two months.

source: Toi t'es dans la Lune, et moi je suis le Soleil
references: ['Worshiper of moons. I am the sun.']
hypothesis: You are in the Moon, and I am the Sun

source: Et j'ai compris que tout est dans la lunette.
references: ['And I finally figured out the trick is right there in the collar.']
hypothesis: And I understood that everything is in the bezel.

source: - C'est à l'ouest, ça.
references: ["That's way out West."]
hypothesis: - That's to the west.

source: On est à l'ouest du Mississippi!
references: ['We are west of the Mississippi!']
hypothesis: We're west of the Mississippi!

source: L'île est à l'ouest de nous, Hugh.
references: ["The island's to the west of us, Hugh."]
hypothesis: The island is west of us, Hugh.

source: Kesan est à l'ouest d'Istanbul, près de la frontière grecque.
references: ['Kesan is West, near the Greek borders.']
hypothesis: Kesan is west of Istanbul, near the Greek border.

source: Nous sommes à l'ouest de votre position.
references: ["We're directly west of you."]
hypothesis: We are west of your position.

source: Je l'ignore, je donne ma langue au chat.
references: ['I do not know, I give my tongue to the cat.']
hypothesis: I ignore it, I give my tongue to the cat.

source: C'est comme essayer d'enfoncer une porte ouverte.
references: ['Blow the door open!']
hypothesis: It's like trying to kick down an open door.

source: Votre pneu est crevé.
references: ["This tire's got a hole in it."]
hypothesis: Your tire is flat.
